text:
Great is thy pow’r, and great thy fame;
Far known and noted is thy name;
And though yon lowin’ heuch be thy home,
Thou travel’st far;
And faith! thou art neither lag nor lame,
Nor blate, nor scaur.

source_text:
Great is thy pow’r an’ great thy fame;
Far ken’d an’ noted is thy name;
An’ tho’ yon lowin’ heuch’s thy hame,
Thou travels far;
An’ faith! thou’s neither lag nor lame,
Nor blate, nor scaur.

text:
E’en swing the dogs, and beat them sicker!
The mair they squeal, aye, thump the thicker;
And still ’mang hands a hearty bicker
O’ something stout;
It gars an owthor’s pulse run quicker,
And sharpens wit.

source_text:
E’en swinge the dogs, and thresh them sicker!
The mair they squeel aye chap the thicker;
And still ’mang hands a hearty bicker
O’ something stout;
It gars an owthor’s pulse beat quicker,
And helps his wit.

